```

…then string-replaces {{user_request}}, {{filtered_catalog_json}}, {{previous_program_or_none}}. Extract just the section between RUNTIME PROMPT START / RUNTIME PROMPT END markers so the manual content below isn't sent to the LLM.

### 3. UI: enable the 'Generate with AI' button in Workouts/index.tsx

Currently disabled at the empty-state CTA (lines ~229-237) with title='AI program generation is on the roadmap.'

Replace with:
- When useLLM().available is false: button stays disabled, tooltip becomes 'Configure an LLM provider in Settings to enable.' Don't pretend it's coming-soon — it's coming-when-the-user-configures.
- When available is true: button is live. Click opens a small modal (or expands inline — match the rest of the tab's idiom) that:
  - Asks for a natural-language phase request (textarea, prefilled with placeholder text guiding what to include — goals, duration, schedule preferences, prior-phase summary)
  - 'Generate' button kicks off generateProgram() with current activeInventory()
  - Shows a loading state ('Generating program…' — generation can take 20-60s for big models)
  - On success: displays a review screen — phase count, exercise count, list of warnings (one line per warning, friendly text not raw findings), then 'Save program' vs 'Discard'
  - 'Save program' calls saveProgram() from state.ts and dismisses
  - On error: shows error inline, 'Try again' button

Match the existing aesthetic — bg-flux-card, rounded-[2rem], the [10px] uppercase-tracked headings.

Add a data-testid hierarchy: 'generate-ai-btn' (already exists), 'generate-ai-modal', 'generate-ai-request', 'generate-ai-submit', 'generate-ai-review', 'generate-ai-save', 'generate-ai-warning-{i}', 'generate-ai-error'.

### 4. Test fixtures and unit tests

Tests for buildFilteredCatalog (in a new tests/programGen.spec.ts or extend an existing file):

- Empty inventory → only 'bodyweight' exercises survive (warmups, mobility, hanging knee raises drop, kettlebell exercises drop).
- Inventory with kettlebell { ownedWeights: [25] } → goblet-squats appears with allowedWeights: [25], kettlebell-swings appears with allowedWeights: [25], kb-gorilla-rows appears (per PR-A's alternatives, KB works) with allowedWeights: [25]. TRX exercises still missing.
- Inventory with kettlebell [25, 35] AND dumbbell [10, 15, 20] → kb-gorilla-rows shows union [10, 15, 20, 25, 35] (since alternatives are DB and DB is owned).
- Inventory with TRX, swedish-ladder, pullup-bar → unweighted exercises present (TRX rows, dead hang, pushups, knee raises); weighted exercises absent.

Tests for generateProgram with a mocked provider:
- Stub configureProvider() with a fake provider whose generate() returns a known JSON string. Confirm:
  - The prompt passed to the fake provider contains the filtered catalog JSON.
  - The prompt does NOT contain unsupported exercises.
  - When the fake provider returns a valid program using only supported exercises → result.warnings is empty.
  - When the fake provider returns a program using an unsupported exercise → result.warnings contains the equipment mismatch.
  - When the fake provider returns malformed JSON → throws with a clear message.
  - When the fake provider returns structurally-broken JSON (missing meta, etc.) → throws with schema errors.

Tests for the UI (Playwright):
- With LLM unavailable: button visible but disabled, tooltip reflects 'configure in Settings'.
- With a mocked LLM provider (window.flux_test_configureLLM hook or similar — match whatever escape hatch the existing test infrastructure uses; if none exists, add a small useLLM().configure escape exposed only under import.meta.env.MODE === 'test'): button enabled, clicking opens the modal, submitting runs the flow, review screen renders, Save persists the program and the workout tab transitions to the loaded-program state.

### 5. Don't regress the manual-paste workflow

The existing prompts/generate-phase.md content is what the user currently pastes into Claude/Gemini manually. After this PR, it MUST still be usable for that purpose. Putting the runtime template at the top and the existing manual content below is exactly the right shape — keep both.

## Constraints & repo conventions (from CLAUDE.md and README)

- NEVER push to main. Open a PR.
- NEVER reference Claude in commits / PR titles / PR descriptions.
- Use nix for ALL commands: `nix develop --command npm …` and `nix develop .#test --command npx playwright test`.
- Run the test suite (`nix develop .#test --command npm test`) before opening the PR and fix any failures.
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, narrow types.
- No new dependencies. Vite's `?raw` import for the prompt template works without anything new.
- Hand-roll the modal — no UI library.

## Out of scope (DO NOT touch)

- Actual LLM provider implementations (BYOK Anthropic/OpenAI/Google, local WebLLM). Per umbrella plan that's a later PR.
- Streaming responses — single Promise<string> is fine for this PR.
- Multi-location program generation (generating a different program per location). The orchestrator reads from activeInventory only; multi-location is forward-compat at the data layer per PR-B but not exposed.

## PR description

Title: 'Wire LLM program generation to filtered catalog and inventory validation' (or similar).

Body: explain PR-C is the final of three landing the equipment-inventory feature. PR-A added the catalog; PR-B added the user inventory + UI. PR-C makes the planner inventory-aware: it sends a filtered catalog (only exercises the user can perform) to the LLM and validates the response against inventory. Note that the LLM provider stack is still stubbed — this PR makes the orchestrator callable; configuring an actual provider remains a separate workstream.

Include a test plan checklist with: 'unit tests pass', 'e2e tests pass', 'manual prompts/generate-phase.md content still usable for paste-into-Claude workflow', 'Generate button shows 'configure in Settings' when no provider available', 'warnings render on the review screen when inventory mismatch'.
